            "heading": "About the role",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "template--18850231484751__f5332588-ee9e-4cb8-b588-7497ef23f2f0-16824067253affbd63-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>You are a rock-star engineer that works on <strong>all product stages from research and development <\/strong>to design and manufacture, making sure that every step through to installation and final commissioning is as smooth as butter. You‚Äôre innovative, you‚Äôre excellent, and your analytical skills are on point.¬†You can work around <strong>CAD methodology<\/strong>, which includes the whole setup: library, parts, materials, 2D drawings, folder structure, etc. Develop new products and improve the existing ones, p<strong>roduce outline designs<\/strong>, design the perfect systems and components, analyze data and interpret the results, and make sure that the product is safe and reliable ‚Äì is there anything you can‚Äôt do?¬†¬†<\/p><p>You're a <strong>creative visionary<\/strong> that knows how to change our innovative ideas into real products. You don't back down from a crazy idea and see it as a challenge to get it working. You'll work closely with our designers, product managers and researchers to <strong>build products that customers love<\/strong>.<\/p><p>You're the master in inventing <strong>mechanical solutions for complex problems<\/strong>. You know the boundaries of plastic injection molding and are eager to discover other production techniques.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "82ff3a37-8cad-430f-95db-9cbdeeef6ec9": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Your know-how is pitch perfect",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "32a98dbe-f634-469b-8904-0f5d2149e699": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>You‚Äôre a regular know-it-all ‚Äì but in a good way. You‚Äôve got a <strong>BSc degree in engineering<\/strong>, as well as proven experience in <strong>consumer goods, electronic goods, and injection molding<\/strong>. You‚Äôve got a great understanding of<strong> CAD methodology,<\/strong> and a sound knowledge of design guides and tolerances for the injection-molding process.¬†¬†<\/p><p>You‚Äôve also got hands-on experience with <strong>Creo<\/strong>, and a familiarity with <strong>2D drawings, 3D engineering files, <\/strong>and<strong> manufacturing documentation<\/strong>. And let‚Äôs not forget your superb <strong>technical writing skills <\/strong>and your solid understanding of the core concepts like mechanics and materials science.¬†¬†<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "d99470d8-e10d-499d-af5b-a48e327e428f": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "You work in harmony with others",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "82e61271-9c1d-4bd4-aee8-3f6ae305e621": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>What we love about you is how much of a <strong>team player <\/strong>you are. You can perform a <strong>full lifecycle of product development<\/strong> in collaboration with a multidisciplinary team of engineers, designers, project managers, product managers, and operational staff.¬†¬†¬†<\/p><p>You‚Äôre always there to support the project manager with <strong>new product development (NPD)<\/strong>, and you are vital when it comes to R&D test set-up support.¬†¬†<\/p><p>Plus, your <strong>communication skills <\/strong>are next level. You can get your technical know-how across in a clear and understandable way, and you‚Äôve got a knack for making sure that the (sometimes crazy) designers‚Äô designs are feasible for production.¬†¬†<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
